#Part 1: Stable spiral, b<a+1
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
a=0.5
b=0.5
N=20000
x=np.linspace(0.01,N/100,N)
#print(x)

y1=np.zeros(len(x))
y2=np.zeros(len(x))

#Plot the nullclines and see if they meet at the correct fixed point or not

for i in range(len(x)):
  y1[i]=(b+1)/(a*x[i])-1/(a*x[i]*x[i])
  y2[i]=b/(a*x[i])
plt.title('Plot of X nullclines and Y nullclines')  
plt.plot(x,y1,label='X nullcline')
plt.plot(x,y2,label='Y nullcline')
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('X axis')
plt.ylabel('Y axis')
plt.xlim((-0,7.5))
plt.ylim((-0,7.5))
plt.show()

xx=[0]*N
yy=[0]*N
t=np.linspace(0.01,N/100,N)
dt=0.01
xx[0]=1
yy[0]=5.01 #Simply plotting the stable spiral
for i in range(N-1):
  xx[i+1]=xx[i]+(1-(b+1)*xx[i]+a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt
  yy[i+1]=yy[i]+(b*xx[i]-a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt
plt.plot(xx,yy,'red')
plt.plot(x,y1,'blue')
plt.plot(x,y2,'green')
plt.title('Plot for a stable spiral')
#plt.xlim((-0.,0.005))
plt.xlim((-1,6))
plt.ylim((-1,7.5))
plt.show()
plt.plot(t,xx,'red',label='x(t)')
#plt.show()
plt.title('Position vs Time Graph')
plt.plot(t,yy,'blue',label='y(t)')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('Position')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec

#w = 3
Y, X = np.mgrid[-1:7.5:100j, -1:6:100j]
U=(1-(b+1)*X+a*X*X*Y)
V=(b*X-a*X*X*Y)
#speed=np.sqrt(U*U+V*V)
#PLotting the stable spiral, the null clines and the trajectory together.
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
gs = gridspec.GridSpec(nrows=3, ncols=2, height_ratios=[2, 2, 2])
ax0 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, 0])
ax0.streamplot(X, Y, U, V,color='aqua')
ax0.set_title('Flow for Brusselator for b<a+1')
plt.plot(x,y1,'green',label='X nullcline')
plt.plot(x,y2,'blue',label='Y nullcline')
plt.xlabel('X coordinate')
plt.ylabel('Y coordinate')
plt.plot(xx,yy,'red',label='Flow towards the stable fixed point.')
plt.legend()
plt.ylim(0,7.5)
plt.xlim(0,6)
plt.show()

        t1=t[i]
        flag=flag+1
    elif(yy[i]>yy[i-1] and yy[i]>yy[i+1] and flag==1):
        t2=t[i]
        break

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

#Classifing the different regions based on the paraneters a and b.

NN=1000
a=[0]*NN
b=[0]*NN
dt=0.01
for i in range(0,NN-1):
    a[i+1]=a[i]+dt
for i in range(0,len(a)):
    b[i]=a[i]+1
g = sns.lineplot(a, b)
plt.fill_between(a, b)
plt.text(6,3,'Stable spirals')
plt.text(2,8,'Stable limit cycles')
plt.xlabel('a')
plt.ylabel('b')
plt.title('Classification of phase space trajectories based\n on values of the parameters a and b')
plt.show()

import math as mt
#bf1=[]
#bf2=[]

#Varialtion of theta vs a, not shown in the report.

ar_a=np.linspace(0.01,4,50)
theta=[0]*len(ar_a)
for i in range(0,len(ar_a)):
    a=ar_a[i]
    b=2
    N=20000
    x=np.linspace(0.01,N/100,N)
    #print(x)

    y1=np.zeros(len(x))
    y2=np.zeros(len(x))

    for i in range(len(x)):
        y1[i]=(b+1)/(a*x[i])-1/(a*x[i]*x[i])
        y2[i]=b/(a*x[i])

    xx=[0]*N
    yy=[0]*N
    t=np.linspace(0.01,N/100,N)
    dt=0.01
    xx[0]=4
    yy[0]=5
    for i in range(N-1):
      xx[i+1]=xx[i]+(1-(b+1)*xx[i]+a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt
      yy[i+1]=yy[i]+(b*xx[i]-a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt

    #w = 3
    Y, X = np.mgrid[-2:7.5:100j, -1:8:100j]
    U=(1-(b+1)*X+a*X*X*Y)
    V=(b*X-a*X*X*Y)
    theta=mt.acos(a/((a*a)+(b*b)))
    count_stable=False
    count_unstable=False
    if(xx[N-1]==xx[N-2] and yy[N-1]==yy[N-1]):
        if(count_stable==False):
            plt.plot(a,theta,'ro')
            count_stable=True
        else:
            plt.plot(a,theta,'ro')
    else:
        if(count_unstable==False):
            plt.plot(a,theta,'bo')
            count_unstable=True
        else:
            plt.plot(a,theta,'bo')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Variation of theta with a')
plt.xlabel('a')
plt.ylabel('theta')
plt.show()

    N=20000

    #print(x)

    y1=np.zeros(len(x))
    y2=np.zeros(len(x))

    for i in range(len(x)):
        y1[i]=(b+1)/(a*x[i])-1/(a*x[i]*x[i])
        y2[i]=b/(a*x[i])
    """

    xx=[0]*N
    yy=[0]*N
    t=np.linspace(0.01,N/100,N)
    dt=0.01
    xx[0]=1
    yy[0]=5.01
    #Subplots used to plot many graphs in one inage
    for i in range(N-1):
        xx[i+1]=xx[i]+(1-(b+1)*xx[i]+a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt
        yy[i+1]=yy[i]+(b*xx[i]-a*xx[i]*xx[i]*yy[i])*dt
    if(iii==1):
        plt.subplot(2,2,1)
        plt.plot(xx,yy,'red')
        #plt.title('Convergence towards a stable fixed point')
        plt.xlim((0,6))
